THE WINES OF GERMANY

The calibre of the 1966 and 1964 vintage on the Rhine and Moselle represents surely the best since 1959. We happily present the famed vineyards and impec- cable growers that have given German wines their great international reputation.

Choose 1966 if you like your wines young, fresh and charming. Choose 1964 for added bottle age and a further touch of subtlety and complexity—some prefer this quieter, less fruity quality. And still remaining are a few authentic survivors of the great 1959 vintage which soon will be destined to become completely unavail- able and a fond memory.
